This paper deals with the problem of maximizing throughput in a cognitive radio system, which involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The system also involves decision-making and optimization (cs.SY), as well as cognitive radio technology (cs.CR). The paper also discusses power allocation strategies, which can be related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
